<i>noun</i>: 순화 [순화], 단일화 [다닐화], 단순화 [단순화], 간편화 [간편화], 간소화 [간소화] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>순화 [순화]</dt><br>
<dd>1. purification</dd><br>
<dd>불순한 것을 없애고 순수하게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of making someone or something pure by eliminating impurities.</dd><br>
<dd>2. simplification</dd><br>
<dd>복잡한 것을 단순하게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of making a complicated thing simple.</dd><br>
<dt>단일화 [다닐화]</dt><br>
<dd>simplification; unification</dd><br>
<dd>여럿인 것이 하나로 됨. 또는 하나로 만듦.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which many different things become one, or the act of unifying many different things into one.</dd><br>
<dt>단순화 [단순화]</dt><br>
<dd>simplification</dd><br>
<dd>복잡하지 않고 간단하게 만듦.</dd><br>
<dd>Making something simple, not complicated.</dd><br>
<dt>간편화 [간편화]</dt><br>
<dd>simplification; making something handy</dd><br>
<dd>간단하고 편리해짐. 또는 그렇게 되게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of something becoming simple and convenient or the act of making such a state.</dd><br>
<dt>간소화 [간소화]</dt><br>
<dd>simplification</dd><br>
<dd>간단하고 소박하게 됨. 또는 그렇게 되게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making something simple and plain, or making such a state.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>